The ascent is made by rail , or horseback , or on foot , as one may prefer . 
This village is at the foot of the mountain . 
We were soon tramping leisurely up the leafy mule path , and then the talk began to flow , as usual . 
no real need for hurry , for the guide book made the walking distance from Wa ggis to the summit only three hours and a quarter . 
