We stopped for a nooning at a strongly built little inn called the Schwarenbach . 
It was the only habitation in the whole Gemmi Pass . 
Close at hand , now , was a chance for a blood curdling Alpine adventure . 
Close at hand was the snowy mass of the Great Altels cooling its topknot in the sky and daring us to an ascent . 
I was fired with the idea , and immediately made up my mind to procure the necessary guides , ropes , etc . 
I instructed Harris to go to the landlord of the inn and set him about our preparations . 
