The corpse belongs to me , and I'll do as I please with him . 
I was leader of the Expedition , and all discoveries achieved by it naturally belonged to me . 
I was entitled to these remains , and could have enforced my right but rather than have bad blood about the matter , I said we would toss up for them . 
I threw heads and won , but it was a barren victory , for although we spent all the next day searching , we never found a bone . 
